ROW.REGULATORY_INTERACTION_NOTE: The site for the RbsR transcriptional regulator in the udk-dcd operon was identified based on genomic Selex analysis |CITS:[23651393]|.

By making use of microarray analysis, it was concluded that FNR activates sbm-argK-ygfGH operon expression under anaerobiosis. A putative FNR-binding site, which was not described in this report, was identified upstream of this operon |CITS: [12754220]|.
ybiJ is induced by hydroquinone, and this induction was inhibited completely in a yhaJ mutant strain |CITS:[ 27713734]|.

By making use of microarray analysis it was concluded that anaerobiosis does not affect expression of the gapC operon, although FNR appears to repress it. A putative FNR-binding site, which was not shown in the report, was identified upstream of this operon |CITS: [12754220]|.

By making use of microarray analyses, Constantinidou et al. |CITS:[16377617]|
concluded that FNR represses ycaC gene expression. They also identified a putative FNR-binding site upstream of the gene, but the sequence was not reported.
ygiD is induced by hydroquinone, and this induction was inhibited completely in a yhaJ mutant strain |CITS:[ 27713734]|.
Mock ionizing radiation conditions induce ydfZ transcription in an FNR-dependent way |CITS: [30673695]|.

The complex of CnuK9E (a variant of Cnu) and HNS antagonizes DNA binding of DicA, causing temperature-dependent filamentous growth at 37oC |CITS:[23028867]|. DicA binds better at 25oC than at 37oC |CITS:[23028867]|.

yhaK is induced by hydroquinone, and this induction is inhibited completely in a yhaJ mutant strain. Furthermore, the induction of yhaK by 2,4-DNT, hydroquinone, and catechol is enhanced in a yhaK mutant strain. This strain showed an accumulation of the 2,4-DNT inducer |CITS:[ 27713734]|.
yhhW is induced by hydroquinone, and this induction was inhibited completely in a yhaJ mutant strain |CITS:[ 27713734]|.

CRP is required for lgoR and lgoD transcription in a sugar-independent manner, irrespective of whether the bacteria are grown with glucose or glucuronate as the main carbon source |CITS: [27129867]|, and this might be due to its cAMP-independent binding to a nonspecific site leading to only a secondary effect |CITS: [8394684]|.
OmpR in its dimeric state binds DNA, but phosphorylation of OmpR is not required |CITS:[29138484]|.
IscR regulates torT expression under aerobic growth conditions |CITS:[29502970]|.

The regulation of CpxR on the yjfN gene has been demonstrated via lacZ reporter gene expression experiments, quantitative PCR analysis of cDNA, and by the identification of a consensus DNA-binding site of CpxR in the regulatory region of yjfN |CITS:[ 23564175]|. The identification of this DNA-binding site was only mentioned in the paper of Raivio et al. (2013), but the DNA sequence was not shown |CITS:[ 23564175]|.
